2) Aggro management<br>
3) Know what you can single pull<br>
4) Know your pets limits(hitpoints, chance of landing root/nuke)<br>
5) Summon Companion<br>
6) Know how to get out(sometimes gating is not fast enough, use exploits if you have to--when soloing in Sebilis I always keep Levitation on, if I somehow  get more than I can handle i will run to the nearest ledge and jump off, while floating down I gate.  I have yet to die doing this because mobs start pathing all over the place trying to get to you.  On a side note I died many times before I figured out how to do this.)<br>
<br>
Basically if you can learn what you can single pull, all you have to worry about is not overnuking but still nuking enough that the mob is going to die before your pet does(or if your real good you can have that finishing nuke casting right when your pet eats it). <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill>The Hunt</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
